Here is a code snipplet which should reproduce the error:

{noformat}
AsynchronousJiraRestClientFactory factory = new AsynchronousJiraRestClientFactory();
JiraRestClient restClient = factory.createWithBasicHttpAuthentication(
                <URL>, <UNAME>, <PWD>);

IssueRestClient issueClient = restClient.getIssueClient();
Issue issue = restClient.getIssueClient().getIssue(issueID).claim();

WorklogInput worklogInput = new WorklogInputBuilder(issue.getSelf()).setStartDate(new DateTime())
    .setComment("updated")
    .setMinutesSpent(1)
    .build();
Promise<Void> result = issueClient.addWorklog(issue.getWorklogUri(), worklogInput);
result.claim();
{noformat}

--> which results in this minutesSpent parameter: 
minutesSpent=1

The problem is that on server side one hour is added instead of one minute.

[EDIT]
Request Body:
{noformat}
WorklogInput{self=null, issueUri=<URI>, author=null, updateAuthor=null, comment=my coment, startDate=2013-08-26T07:00:03.000+02:00, minutesSpent=1, visibility=null, adjustEstimate=AUTO, adjustEstimateValue=null}
{noformat}

